<br>

<div class="section">Welcome to Ninf Home Page</div>

<div class="abstract">
Ninf is a Japanese project developing programming middleware which
enables users to access various resources such as hardware, software and
scientific data on the Grid with an easy-to-use interface.
<br>
Ninf-G is an open source software which supports development and
execution of Grid-enabled applications using Grid Remote Procedure
Call (GridRPC) on distributed computing resources.
<br>
</div>
<br>
<div class="section"> <img align="middle" src="image/Lecture.gif" width="20"> About Ninf-G </div>
<strong>
<div class="section_contents">
Ninf-G is a reference implementation of Grid RPC system using the <a
href="http://www.globus.org/">Globus Toolkit</a>.  Ninf-G provides
Grid RPC APIs which are discussed for the standardization at the <a
href="https://forge.gridforum.org/projects/gridrpc-wg/">Grid Remote Procedure Call Working Group</a> of the <a
href="http://www.globalgridforum.org/">Global Grid Forum</a>.  The
details of the standardization of the Grid RPC APIs is reported on the
<a href="http://www.eece.unm.edu/~apm/docs/APM_GridRPC_0702.pdf"> GGF
Working Group Document</a>.
A part of the development of Ninf-G2 was supported by a grant from the Ministry of Education, Sports, Culture, Science and Technology (MEXT) of Japan through the <a href="http://www.naregi.org/">NAREGI (National Research Grid Initiative)</a> Project.<br>
</div>
<ul>
<li> related links
  <ul>
  <li> <a href="http://www.naregi.org">NAREGI</a>
  <li> <a href="http://www.ggf.org/">Global Grid Forum</a>
  <li> <a href="https://forge.gridforum.org/projects/gridrpc-wg/">GGF Advanced Programming Models Research Group</a>
  <li> <a href="http://www.eece.unm.edu/~apm/docs/APM_GridRPC_0702.pdf">GridRPC:
  A Remote Procedure Call API for Grid Computing</a>
  <li> <a href="http://icl.cs.utk.edu/netsolve">NetSolve</a>: A
  reference implementation of Grid RPC APIs.
  </ul>
</ul>
</strong>
